A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend an Act to provide an additional homestead exemption from Gwinnett County
2 school district ad valorem taxes for educational purposes in the amount of $2,000.00 of the
3 assessed value of the homestead for residents of that school district who are certain public
4 service employees, approved May 3, 2023 (Ga. L. 2023, p. 4346), so as to expand such
5 exemption to disabled veterans and all employees of the Gwinnett County School District
6 and the Buford City School District; to provide for compliance with constitutional
7 requirements; to provide for a referendum, effective dates, and automatic repeal; to provide
8 for mandatory execution of election and judicial remedies regarding failure to comply; to
9 provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
11 SECTION 1.
12 An Act to provide an additional homestead exemption from Gwinnett County school district
13 ad valorem taxes for educational purposes in the amount of $2,000.00 of the assessed value
14 of the homestead for residents of that school district who are certain public service
15 employees, approved May 3, 2023 (Ga. L. 2023, p. 4346), is amended by revising
16 paragraph (3) of subsection (a) of Section 1 as follows:
