17 "(3) 'Public service employee' means a person who is, on or before January 1 of the year
18 in which application for the exemption under subsection (b) of this section is made, a:
19 (A) Firefighter, paramedic, certified peace officer, or other law enforcement officer
20 employed by the government of the United States or any department, agency, authority,
21 or bureau thereof or by the State of Georgia or any county, municipality, special
22 district, county or independent school system, or other political subdivision thereof;
23 (B) Person employed by the Gwinnett County School District or Buford City School
24 District;
25 (C) Person employed by or holding staff privileges at a hospital located within
26 Gwinnett County;
27 (D) Member of the armed forces of the United States, including any reserve or
28 National Guard components and the United States Coast Guard; or
29 (E) Disabled veteran as defined by Code Section 48-5-48 of the Official Code of
30 Georgia Annotated."
31 SECTION 2.
32 In accordance with the requirements of Article VII, Section II of the Constitution of the State
33 of Georgia, this Act shall not become law unless it receives the requisite two-thirds' majority
34 vote in both the Senate and the House of Representatives.
35 SECTION 3.
36 The election superintendent of Gwinnett County shall call and conduct an election as
37 provided in this section for the purpose of submitting this Act to the electors of the Gwinnett
38 County school district for approval or rejection. The election superintendent shall conduct
39 that election on the date of the general primary in 2026 and shall issue the call and conduct
40 such election as provided by general law. The election superintendent shall cause the date
41 and purpose of the election to be published once a week for two weeks immediately
