42 preceding the date thereof in the official organ of Gwinnett County. The ballot shall have
43 written or printed thereon the words:
44 "( ) YES Shall the existing additional $2,000.00 homestead exemption from Gwinnett
45 ( ) NO County School District ad valorem taxes for education purposes for certain
46 public service employees be expanded to also apply to disabled veterans and
47 all employees of the Gwinnett County School District and the Buford City
48 School District?"
49 All persons desiring to vote for approval of the Act shall vote "Yes," and all persons desiring
50 to vote for rejection of the Act shall vote "No." If more than one-half of the votes cast on
51 such question are for approval of the Act, Section 1 of this Act shall become of full force and
52 effect on January 1, 2027. If the Act is not so approved or if the election is not conducted
53 as provided in this section, Section 1 of this Act shall not become effective, and this Act shall
54 be automatically repealed on the 365th calendar day following the election date provided for
55 in this section. The expense of such election shall be borne by Gwinnett County. It shall be
56 the election superintendent's duty to certify the result thereof to the Secretary of State. The
57 provisions of this section shall be mandatory upon the election superintendent and are not
58 intended as directory. If the election superintendent fails or refuses to comply with this
59 section, any elector of the Gwinnett County school district may apply for a writ of mandamus
60 to compel the election superintendent to perform his or her duties under this section. If the
61 court finds that the election superintendent has not complied with this section, the court shall
62 fashion appropriate relief requiring the election superintendent to call and conduct such
63 election on the date required by this section or on the next date authorized for special
64 elections provided for in Code Section 21-2-540 of the O.C.G.A.
65 SECTION 4.
66 Except as otherwise provided in Section 3 of this Act, this Act shall become effective upon
67 its approval by the Governor or upon its becoming law without such approval.
